# WeChat SVG Interactive Generator

Generate interactive SVG content optimized for WeChat Official Accounts (å¾®ä¿¡å…¬ä¼—å·). Output can be directly pasted into WeChat editor with full animation and click interaction support.

## âš ï¸ Critical WeChat Limitations

WeChat has strict SVG restrictions. **Everything below is essential reading:**

### ğŸš« What WeChat DOES NOT Support

| Limitation | Details |
|------------|---------|
| **No JavaScript** | Not even one line. Zero JS allowed. |
| **No CSS Animations** | `@keyframes` and `transition` are completely ignored |
| **No id.click triggers** | `begin="element.click"` does NOT work |
| **No Color Gradients** | `<linearGradient>` and `<radialGradient>` are stripped |
| **Unreliable Timed Animations** | `begin="2s"` and delays don't work on mobile |
| **clipPath Overflow** | Images clipped with clipPath will bleed outside rounded corners |

### âœ… Verified Solutions

#### 1. Click Triggers: Use `mousedown` Instead of `id.click`

```xml
<!-- âŒ WRONG - Does not work in WeChat -->
<animate attributeName="opacity" begin="button.click" dur="0.3s" from="0" to="1"/>

<!-- âœ… CORRECT - Use mousedown directly on the element -->
<animate attributeName="opacity" begin="mousedown" dur="0.3s" from="0" to="1"/>
```

#### 2. Rounded Images: Use Pattern Instead of clipPath

```xml
<!-- âŒ WRONG - Image bleeds outside rounded corners in WeChat -->
<clipPath id="roundClip">
  <rect width="160" height="160" rx="80"/>
</clipPath>
<image href="photo.jpg" clip-path="url(#roundClip)"/>

<!-- âœ… CORRECT - Pattern fill method -->
<pattern id="photoPattern" patternUnits="objectBoundingBox" width="1" height="1">
  <image href="photo.jpg" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid slice" width="160" height="160"/>
</pattern>
<rect width="160" height="160" rx="80" fill="url(#photoPattern)"/>
```

#### 3. Animations: Use SMIL with mousedown/mouseup

```xml
<!-- Button scale effect on click -->
<g>
  <rect id="btn" width="200" height="60" rx="30" fill="#ff6b35"/>
  <animate xlink:href="#btn" attributeName="transform"
           type="scale" begin="mousedown" end="mouseup"
           from="1" to="0.95" dur="0.1s" fill="freeze"/>
</g>

<!-- Reveal hidden content -->
<g id="hiddenContent" opacity="0">
  <text>Hidden Message!</text>
  <animate attributeName="opacity" begin="mousedown" dur="0.5s" from="0" to="1"/>
</g>
```

#### 4. No Gradients: Use Solid Colors or Masks

```xml
<!-- âŒ WRONG - Gradients are stripped -->
<linearGradient id="btnGrad">...</linearGradient>
<rect fill="url(#btnGrad)"/>

<!-- âœ… CORRECT - Use solid colors with overlay -->
<rect width="200" height="60" rx="30" fill="#ff6b35"/>
```

## Capabilities

- **Click Interactions**: Multi-step clickable flows, button responses, state changes
- **SMIL Animations**: Native SVG animations (the only way in WeChat)
- **WeChat Compatibility**: Uses `mousedown`/`mouseup` triggers exclusively
- **Pattern-based Rounded Images**: Reliable image clipping for WeChat
- **Preset Templates**: Mac Terminal, Cyberpunk, Minimal, Glassmorphism, Retro
- **HTML Preview**: Generates standalone HTML file for browser preview
- **Copy to Clipboard**: One-click SVG copy for WeChat editor

