## Template Styles

### Mac Terminal
- Dark background (#1e1e1e)
- Green/blue syntax highlighting
- Monospace fonts (SF Mono/Consolas)
- Command prompt styling (`>`, `$`)
- Blinking cursor animation (using SMIL)
- Solid colors only (no gradients)

### Cyberpunk
- Neon pink/cyan colors
- Glow effects via SVG filters
- Grid backgrounds (pattern)
- Scanline overlays
- Glitch animations (SMIL)
- Solid colors only

### Minimal
- Clean white/light gray
- Subtle shadows via solid colors
- Simple typography
- Smooth transitions via SMIL
- Rounded corners (rx/ry)

### Glassmorphism (Adapted for WeChat)
- Frosted glass effect (simulated with semi-transparent fills)
- Blurred backgrounds (avoid - use solid colors)
- Gradient overlays (avoid - use solid colors)
- Semi-transparent elements
- Soft shadows (avoid - use solid colors)

### Retro
- Warm color palette (solid colors)
- Pixel-style elements
- Scanline textures (pattern)
- CRT monitor effect
- VHS color shifting (avoid - use solid colors)

## Output Format

The generator produces:
1. **HTML Preview File** - Standalone `.html` file with full functionality
2. **SVG Code** - Extracted SVG code ready for WeChat pasting
3. **Copy Button** - In the HTML preview, click to copy SVG

## WeChat Compatibility Notes

- WeChat uses `mousedown`/`mouseup` instead of CSS `:active`
- Use `setPointerEvents()` to handle touch/click events
- Avoid JavaScript - use CSS animations and SMIL
- Max recommended size: 500x600px for article embeds
- Use `cursor: pointer` for clickable elements
- Include `xlink:href` for backward compatibility

## Complete WeChat-Compatible Example

```xml
<svg viewBox="0 0 400 600" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">

  <!-- Background: Solid color (no gradient) -->
  <rect width="400" height="600" fill="#1a1a2e"/>

  <!-- Rounded Avatar using Pattern -->
  <defs>
    <pattern id="avatarPattern" patternUnits="objectBoundingBox"
             width="1" height="1">
      <image href="https://example.com/avatar.jpg"
             preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid slice"
             width="120" height="120"/>
    </pattern>
    <!-- Pulse animation -->
    <filter id="glow">
      <feGaussianBlur stdDeviation="3" result="coloredBlur"/>
      <feMerge>
        <feMergeNode in="coloredBlur"/>
        <feMergeNode in="SourceGraphic"/>
      </feMerge>
    </filter>
  </defs>

  <!-- Avatar Circle -->
  <circle cx="200" cy="120" r="60" fill="url(#avatarPattern)"/>

  <!-- Title -->
  <text x="200" y="220" text-anchor="middle" font-family="sans-serif"
        font-size="28" font-weight="bold" fill="#ffffff">
    ç‚¹å‡»é¢†å–ç¥ç¦
  </text>

  <!-- Interactive Button -->
  <g id="button" style="cursor: pointer">
    <!-- Button Background -->
    <rect x="100" y="280" width="200" height="60" rx="30" fill="#ff6b35"/>

    <!-- Button Text -->
    <text x="200" y="318" text-anchor="middle"
          font-family="sans-serif" font-size="18" fill="#ffffff">
      ç«‹å³é¢†å–
    </text>

    <!-- Scale Animation on Click (mousedown/mouseup) -->
    <animateTransform xlink:href="#button"
                      attributeName="transform" type="scale"
                      begin="mousedown" end="mouseup"
                      from="1" to="0.95" dur="0.1s" fill="freeze"/>
  </g>

  <!-- Hidden Result (reveals on click) -->
  <g id="result" opacity="0">
    <rect x="50" y="400" width="300" height="120" rx="10" fill="#16213e"/>
    <text x="200" y="450" text-anchor="middle"
          font-family="sans-serif" font-size="16" fill="#58a6ff">
      æ­å–œè·å¾—æ–°å¹´ç¥ç¦!
    </text>
    <text x="200" y="480" text-anchor="middle"
          font-family="sans-serif" font-size="14" fill="#c9d1d9">
      æ„Ÿè°¢æ‚¨çš„å‚ä¸
    </text>

    <!-- Reveal Animation -->
    <animate attributeName="opacity" begin="mousedown" dur="0.5s"
             from="0" to="1" fill="freeze"/>
  </g>

</svg>
```

## Common Patterns Reference

### Pattern 1: Click to Reveal
```xml
<g id="content" opacity="0">
  <text>Hidden</text>
  <animate attributeName="opacity" begin="mousedown" dur="0.3s" from="0" to="1"/>
</g>
```

### Pattern 2: Click to Toggle
```xml
<g id="toggleContent">
  <animate attributeName="opacity" values="0;1;0" dur="0.5s" begin="mousedown"/>
</g>
```

### Pattern 3: Click to Scale
```xml
<g id="btn">
  <rect width="100" height="40" rx="20" fill="#ff6b35"/>
  <animateTransform attributeName="transform" type="scale"
                     begin="mousedown" end="mouseup" from="1" to="0.9"/>
</g>
```

### Pattern 4: Sequential Animation
```xml
<g id="step2" opacity="0">
  <text>Step 2</text>
  <animate attributeName="opacity" begin="mousedown+0.3s" dur="0.3s" from="0" to="1"/>
</g>
```

### Pattern 5: Loop Animation
```xml
<g>
  <circle cx="200" cy="300" r="20" fill="#ff6b35">
    <animate attributeName="r" values="20;30;20" dur="1.5s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
  </circle>
</g>
```

### Pattern 6: Click Trigger Multiple
```xml
<rect id="btn" width="150" height="50" rx="25" fill="#58a6ff"/>
<animate xlink:href="#btn" attributeName="fill" begin="mousedown" dur="0.2s" to="#ff6b35"/>
<animate xlink:href="#btn" attributeName="fill" begin="mouseup" dur="0.2s" to="#58a6ff"/>
```

